        "question": "Question 1: Complete the notes (____)",
        "passage": "LY: Good morning. Thanks for coming in to see us here at the agency, Joe. I'm one of the agency representatives, and my name's Sally Baker.\n\nOE: Hi Sally. I think we spoke on the phone, didn't we?\n\nLY: That's right, we did. So thank you for sending in your CV. We've had quite a careful look at it and I think we have two jobs that might be suitable for you.\n\nLY: The first one is in a company based in North London. They're looking for an administrative assistant.\n\nLY: They're called Home Solutions and they design and make furniture.\n\nOE: Oh, I don't know much about that, but it sounds interesting.\n\nLY: Yes, well as I said, they want someone in their office, and looking at your past experience it does look as if you fit quite a few of the requirements. So on your CV it appears you've done some data entry?\n\nLY: So that's one skill they want. Then they expect the person they appoint to attend meetings and take notes there ...\n\nLY: And you'd need to be able to cope with general admin.\n\nOE: Filling, and keeping records and so on? That should be OK. And in my last job I also had to manage the diary.\n\nLY: Excellent. That's something they want here too. I'd suggest you add it to your CV – I don't think you mentioned that, did you?\n\nLY: So as far as the requirements go, they want good computer skills, of course, and they particularly mention spreadsheets.\n\nLY: And interpersonal skills – which would be something they'd check with your references.\n\nLY: Then they mention that they want someone who is careful and takes care with details – just looking at your CV, I'd say you're probably alright there.\n\nOE: I think so, yes. Do they want any special experience?\n\nLY: I think they wanted some experience of teleconferencing.\n\nLY: let's see, yes, good. In fact they're only asking for at least one year, so that's great. So is that something that might interest you?\n\nOE: It is, yes. The only thing is, you said they were in North London so it would be quite a long commute for me.",
