        "passage": "AN: Oh, hi. I saw your advertisement about copying pictures to disk and I'd like a bit more information about what you do.\n\nAN: Well, I've got a box full of old family photos that's been up in the attic for years, some of them must be 50 or 60 years old, and I'd like to get them converted to digital format.\n\nAN: Right. And what about size? The photos are all sorts of sizes – are there any restrictions?\n\nEE: Well the maximum size of photo we can do with our normal services is 30 centimetres. And each picture must be a least 4 centimetres, that's the minimum we can cope with.\n\nAN: That should be fine. And some of them are in a frame – should I take them out before I send them?\n\nEE: Yes please, we can't copy them otherwise. And also the photos must all be separate, they mustn't be stuck into an album.\n\nAN: OK, that's not a problem. So can you give me an idea of how much this will cost? I've got about 360 photos I think.\n\nEE: We charge £195 for 300 to 400 photos for the basic service.\n\nEE: Yes, one disk – but you can get extra ones for £5 each.\n\nAN: That's good. So do I need to pay when I send you the photos?\n\nEE: No, we won't need anything until we've actually copied the pictures. Then we'll let you know how much it is, and once we've received the payment, we'll send the parcel off to you.",
