        "passage": "ON: Hi Shannon – how are you settling into your new flat?\n\nON: Yes, I am. My cousins are coming to stay for a couple of days, and I have to cook for them.\n\nON: Well, there's plenty of places to buy food in Kite Place – it's the area by the harbour.\n\nON: Well, neither of them eats meat but they both like fish.\n\nON: It's at the far end of Kite Place, so you have to go over the bridge and then it's on the right.\n\nON: It doesn't close until four, but I'd recommend going earlier than that – it does run out of some things.\n\nON: As long as you get there by 3.30, you should be fine. It's only 11 now, so plenty of time.\n\nON: I do, and I want to avoid all the plastic packaging in the supermarket!\n\nON: Well, there's a really nice organic shop there. Now what's it called … it's the name of a flower. I know, it's 'Rose'.\n\nON: Yeah – it sells vegetables and quite a lot of other stuff.\n\nON: Well, as you reach the market, you'll see a big grey building on your left – I think it used to be a warehouse. Anyway, now it's a restaurant upstairs, but the ground floor has two shops either side of the entrance and it's the one on the left.\n\nON: You can't miss it – there's also a big sign on the pavement so you can look for that.\n\nON: Fine! I guess if I need anything else, I'll have to go to the supermarket.\n\nON: Yeah – you should be able to get everything you need, but there's a minibus that goes to the supermarket if you need it. It's purple and the number is 289.\n\nON: So what do you need to get at the fish market? The salmon is always very good and the shellfish.\n\nON: I'm going to make a curry, I think, and I need about 12 prawns for that.\n\nON: It's a type of seaweed. I just ask for a handful and you fry it in butter. It's delicious!\n\nON: Great – it's always good to try something different.\n\nON: I'll see what beans they have in the organic shop and I think I'll get something for dessert there.\n\nON: I'm not sure – they're not always ripe. I'd prefer a melon – it's bigger too.\n\nON: Good idea. The owner also sells a lot of spices there that you can put in a curry, and things like coconut.\n\nON: I know bread doesn't really go with curry but I always like to have some in case.\n\nON: As I said – all the bread is home-made and there's lots of variety. I like the brown bread myself.\n\nON: Well – not that, but they have a whole range of tarts and the best are the strawberry ones.\n\nON: Perfect – hopefully I won't even have to go to the supermarket!",
